 *
 * \subsection configuration_line Configuration line
 *
 * Configurations can appear in the file standalone. In this case, the full path
 * to the configuration is necessary.
 *
 * \par Specification
 *
 * <pre>
 *   <config-spec> ::= <opt-whitespace> <key-path> <whitespace> <key-value> <line-end>
 * </pre>
 *
 * \par Examples
 *
 * \todo Explain examples.
 *
 * <pre>
 *   path:to:key value
 * </pre>
 * <pre>
 *   just_a_key    value
 * </pre>
 * <pre>
 *   key   a multiword value
 * </pre>
 *
 * \subsection configuration_partial Partial configuration declarations
 *
 * Configuration lines can also be abbreviated. They are used within other
 * blocks to help abbreviate configuration specifications.
 *
 * \par Specification
 *
 * <pre>
 *   <partial-config-spec> ::= <opt-whitespace> <separator> <config-spec> <line-end>
 *   <partial-configs>     ::= <partial-config-spec> <partial-config> | <partial-config-spec>
 * </pre>
 *
 * \par Examples
