 *
 * \subsection group_block Group block
 *
 * A group is a collection of processes which can be treated as a single
 * process for connection and configuration purposes. A group is just a
 * declaration of ports with internal connections, and a set of available
 * configuration values. Mappings may also have flags associated with them. The
 * currently understood flags are:
 *
 * \mflag{required} Marks the port as required for the group.
 *
 * \par Specification
 *
 * <pre>
 *   <map-flag>            ::= <alpha> <map-flag> | <alpha>
 *   <map-flags>           ::= <map-flag> <map-separator> <map-flag> | <map-flag>
 *   <map-flag-decl>       ::= <flag-start> <map-flags> <flag-close>
 *   <map-options>         ::= <map-flag-decl> | ""
 *   <map-decl>            ::= "map" <map-options>
 *   <input-mapping-spec>  ::= <opt-whitespace> <map-decl> <whitespace> "from" <whitespace> <port-name> <line-end>
 *                             <opt-whitespace> "to" <port-addr> <line-end>
 *   <output-mapping-spec> ::= <opt-whitespace> <map-decl> <whitespace> "from" <whitespace> <port-addr> <line-end>
 *                             <opt-whitespace> "to" <port-name> <line-end>
 *   <group-decl>          ::= <partial-config-spec> | <input-mapping-spec> | <output-mapping-spec>
 *   <group-decls>         ::= <group-decl> <group-decls> | ""
 *   <group-block-spec>    ::= <opt-whitespace> "group" <whitespace> <key-component> <line-end>
 *                             <group-decls>
 * </pre>
 *
